Figure 2 shows the room temperature absorption UV-NIR spectra for the PbS synthesized in castor oil and ricinoleic acid at 280 °C. The absorption spectra show relatively sharp absorption excitonic peaks at approximately 1875, 1895, and 1930 nm for CSTO-capped PbS NCs (Fig. 2a) and 1900, 2015, and 2045 nm for RA-capped PbS NCs (Fig. 2b). These excitonic peaks show large quantum confinement inducing blue shift of the absorption edges compared to bulk PbS (3100 nm). The blueshift decreases with increasing growth period. The size of the PbS particles was calculated using Eq. 1 [31] on the basis of absorption excitonic peaks (nm) deduced from Fig. 2a, b.1Eg=Egb+1aS2+bS,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
